example data with 2000 observations of 2 continuous variables

Source: R/Data.R
ExampleData.Rd

A simulated data set containing 2 continuous variables.

data(ExampleData)

Format

A list containing the following elements:

z

simulated continuous covariate V1 and V2. The true time-independent function is \(\beta(t)=1\) and the true time-varying function is \(\beta(t)=sin(3\pi t/4).\)

event

simulated failure event response; binary variable with 0 or 1.

time

simulated observed event time; continuous variable with non-negative values.
